         <abstract>
            <p>A dramatic movement is now taking place within the U. S. life insurance industry--a movement so broad and so sweeping it may constitute a revolution. The variable annuities and mutual funds that life insurance companies are beginning to market represent the entrance of one of America's oldest and largest industries into an entirely new field. The results may be explosive. The author traces the historical development of the movement, assesses the progress of the industry to date, examines the potential impact of the insurance industry's entrance into the equity field.</p>
          </abstract>
